<subSubSection pageNumber="719" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="719">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="719">Note:</emphasis>
The taxonomic identity of the type has provoked differences of opinion, with many authors (e.g. Howard &amp; Staples in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="719">J. Arnold Arbor.</emphasis>
64: 513. 1983) treating it as 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Herb." authorityName="Herb." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Hymenocallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carolinianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="719">Hymenocallis carolinianum</emphasis>
(L.) Herb.
</taxonomicName>
but others (e.g. Smith &amp; Garland in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="719">Taxon</emphasis>
52: 814. 2003) arguing that it is a depiction of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Pancratium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritimum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="719">Pancratium maritimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
